Originated at Don the Beachcomber as the Macadamia Nut Chi Chi, with multiple sources (PUNCH, Bamboo Sam's, The Kitchn, A Couple Cooks, Cocktail Party app) confirming Donn Beach as the creator rather than Harry Yee. "Chi Chi" is pidgin for "mother's milk." Essentially a Piña Colada made with vodka instead of rum; the simplified three-ingredient version below is the 1970s adaptation that most bars serve today, dropping the original macadamia nut liqueur.

In a #blender{} combine @vodka{1.5%oz}, @cream of coconut{1%oz} (Coco López), @pineapple juice{4%oz}, and @crushed ice{1%cup}.

Blend on high speed until smooth and slushy, about 15 seconds.

Pour into a chilled #hurricane glass{} or large goblet.

Garnish with a @pineapple wedge{1} and a @maraschino cherry{1}.
